                    <ab> In nomine [domini] Dei eterni. <persName ref="#people/21"
                            key="#Emperor/king">Berengarius</persName> divina favente clementia <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus. Si petitionibus fidelium
                        nostrorum libenter annuimus, devotiores eos ad nostre fideIitatis obsequia
                        reddimus. Quocirca omnium universalis Ecclesie fidelium nostrorum videlicet
                        presentium ac futurorum noverit industria, qualiter <persName
                            key="#Count #Intercessory #Marquis/duke" ref="#people/1502">Odelricus</persName>
                        illuster <rs key="#Marquis/duke">marchio</rs> sacrique palatii nostri <rs
                            key="#Count">comes</rs> et dilectus fidelis noster <rs
                            key="#Intercessory">suppliciter</rs> nostram exoravit maiestatem,
                        quatinus ob amorem superne remunerationis per nostri precepti paginam
                        quoddam <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs> infra <rs key="#Cities"
                            >civitatem</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/43" key="#Cities">Placentinam</placeName> a beate
                        videIicet memorie <persName key="#Queen" ref="#people/55"
                            >Angilberga</persName>
                        <rs key="#Queen">imperatrice</rs> constructum et in honore <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/53" key="#Monasteries">Sancti Sisti</orgName>
                        dedicatum <persName ref="#people/67">Berte</persName> dilectissime filie
                        nostre cum omnibus suis pertinenciis confirmare dignaremur, simul quoque
                        roborantes et in perpetuum concedentes eidem monasterio quasdam <rs
                            key="#Curtes">curtes</rs>
                        <geogName ref="#estates/40"
                            key="#Mountains #Curtes #Forests #Fisheries #Mills #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Markets #Districtio #Aldius #Royal_slave"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/33"
                                key="#Mountains #Curtes #Forests #Fisheries #Mills #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Markets #Districtio #Aldius #Royal_slave"
                                >Guardastallam</placeName></geogName> scilicet, <geogName
                            ref="#estates/38"
                            key="#Mountains #Curtes #Forests #Fisheries #Mills #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Markets #Districtio #Aldius #Royal_slave"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/32"
                                key="#Mountains #Curtes #Forests #Fisheries #Mills #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Markets #Districtio #Aldius #Royal_slave"
                                >Lucariam</placeName></geogName>, <geogName ref="#estates/77"
                            key="#Mountains #Curtes #Forests #Fisheries #Mills #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Markets #Districtio #Aldius #Royal_slave"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/361"
                                key="#Mountains #Curtes #Forests #Fisheries #Mills #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Markets #Districtio #Aldius #Royal_slave"
                                >Littora Paludiana</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            ref="#estates/80"
                            key="#Mountains #Curtes #Forests #Fisheries #Mills #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Markets #Districtio #Aldius #Royal_slave"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/362"
                                key="#Mountains #Curtes #Forests #Fisheries #Mills #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Markets #Districtio #Aldius #Royal_slave"
                                >Villole</placeName></geogName>, <geogName ref="#estates/42"
                            key="#Mountains #Curtes #Forests #Fisheries #Mills #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Markets #Districtio #Aldius #Royal_slave"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/34"
                                key="#Mountains #Curtes #Forests #Fisheries #Mills #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Markets #Districtio #Aldius #Royal_slave"
                                >Piguniariam</placeName></geogName>, <geogName ref="#estates/207"
                            key="#Mountains #Curtes #Forests #Fisheries #Mills #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Markets #Districtio #Aldius #Royal_slave"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/462"
                                key="#Mountains #Curtes #Forests #Fisheries #Mills #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Markets #Districtio #Aldius #Royal_slave"
                                >Curtem Novam</placeName></geogName> atque <geogName
                            ref="#estates/110"
                            key="#Mountains #Curtes #Forests #Fisheries #Mills #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Markets #Districtio #Aldius #Royal_slave"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/141"
                                key="#Mountains #Curtes #Forests #Fisheries #Mills #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Markets #Districtio #Aldius #Royal_slave"
                                >Campum Miliacium</placeName>
                        </geogName>et omnia quecumque memorata imperatrix per <rs key="#Testamentum"
                            >institutionis sue paginam</rs> ubique idem cenobium diffinivit
                        habendum. Cuius petitionem tota devotione suscipientes, id fieri annuimus,
                        hoc nostrum preceptum scribi iubentes, per quod prelibate filie nostre idem
                        monasterium confirmamus, quatenus in sua sit potestate et dominio quousque
                        vixerit et ibidem domina et ordinatrix atque rectrix invigilet ac permaneat
                        donec eius fuerit vita. Per quod etiam iam prescripto venerabili loco
                        concedimus ac confirmamus omnes res et possessiones mobiles ac immobiles tam
                        per cartulas quamque extra cartulas vel cuiuseumque inscriptionis titulo ad
                        partem ipsius monasterii legibus acquisitas et aequirendas seu quidquid per
                        regum vel imperatorum antecessorum nostrorum <rs
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">precepta</rs> ad eundem sacrum locum
                        collatum est, atque <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellulam</rs> quandam que
                        antiquitus <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/1508"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            >Monasterium</orgName> dicebatur non procul a Placentina urbe silam loco
                        qui <placeName ref="#places/14"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Caput Trebie</placeName> vocatur, in qua <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1503"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            >ecclesia apostolorum principis</orgName> honore dicata consistit, cum
                        omnibus inibi pertinentibus, quemadmodum <persName ref="#people/80"
                            key="#Emperor/king">Karlomannus</persName> serenissimus rex et
                        consobrinus noster eandem cellulam cum universis appendiciis suis eidem
                        monasterio <rs key="#Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure">proprietario iure</rs>
                        largitus est, prenominato venerabili loco per hoc nostre imperialis
                        auctoritatis preceptum ex integro perdonamus, largimur, confirmamus, ac
                        modis omnibus corroboramus. Familias quoque utriusque sexus et conditionis
                        cum curtibus et <rs key="#Churches/religious_bodies">capellis</rs> earumque
                        appendiciis cum omnibus <rs key="#Castle">castellis</rs>, casis, <rs
                            key="#Wine">vineis</rs>, <rs key="#Cereals">campis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Hay/fodder">pascuis</rs>, pratis, <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs>,
                        salectis, sationibus, paludibus, aquis aquarumque decursibus, <rs
                            key="#Mills">molendinis</rs>, <rs key="#Rivers">fluminibus</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Fisheries">piscationibus</rs>, ripis, rupinis, <rs
                            key="#Mountains">montibus</rs>, collibus, vallibus ac planiciebus,
                        cultis et incultis, divisis et indivisis, <rs key="#Markets"
                            >mercationibus</rs>, vectigalibus, <rs key="#Districtio"
                            >districtionibus</rs>, <rs key="#Royal_slave">servis et ancillis</rs>,
                            <rs key="#Royal_aldius">aldiis et aldianis</rs> et omnibus que dici aut
                        nominari possunt ad idem monasterium iuste et legaliter respicientibus in
                        integrum confirmamus, ita videlicet, ut prelibata filia nostra quousque
                        vixerit hac nostra auctoritate roborata de prescriptis rebus eidem
                        monasterio pertinentibus tam per preceptorum paginam, ut diximus, quamque
                        per aliarum istrumenta cartarum et acquisitis et acquirendis potestative
                        faciat, omnium magnarum parvarumque personarum molestatione remota. Si quis
                        vero hanc nostram auctoritatem violare temptaverit, <rs key="#Penalty">CL
                            libras auri optimi </rs>componere cogatur, medietatem <rs
                            key="#Camera_regis">camere nostre</rs> et medietatem iam dicte filie
                        nostre. Quod ut verius credatur diligentiusque ab omnibus observetur, manu
                        propria roborantes de annulo nostro iussimus insigniri. Signum domni (M.)
                        Berengarii piissimi imperatoris. <persName ref="#people/1501"
                            key="#Chancellor #Bishops">Iohannes</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> et <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs>
                        ad vicem <persName ref="#people/216" key="#Archchancellor #Bishops"
                            >Ardengi</persName> episcopi et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii</rs> recognovi et subscripsi. Dat. VI. kal. septembr.,
                        anno dominice incarnationis DCCCCXVI, domni vero Berengarii piissimi regis
                        XXVIII, imperii autem sui secundo, indictione V. Actum in <geogName
                            ref="#estates/2318">curte <placeName ref="#places/725"
                            >Sinna</placeName></geogName>, in Christi nomine feliciter, amen. </ab>
